Rating: 2
This potato salad is mediocre. It isn't that potato salad you had at a potluck one time that you can't forget and keeps you trying different potato salad recipes to find the same one. Keep moving folks...nothing to see here. I decided to make this because it used dill. I was cooking for some Germans --and Germans think Americans put sugar in everything so I didn't want to use a recipe with sweet pickles. I added extra dill juice on the potatoes as another reviewer suggested, but it was just plain lacking. Bore me to death with this recipe!

Rating: 4
Although there are many other great potato salads out there, this version requires only a half an hour of chilling so can be made nearly as an afterthought and still tastes wonderful. Potatoes and celery dominate. I peeled and chopped the potatoes and boiled them while I prepared the rest of the ingredients and had the salad made in 15 minutes.

Rating: 4
We love this recipe!! I prefer to add extra sweet pickles, chopped, as well as extra yellow mustard or a combo of yellow mustard and dijon. I omit the celery and chop up a sweet red bell pepper for color and contrast. For special occasions, I add 3-4 pieces of crumbled bacon. YUM. Boyfriend swears it's the best he's ever tasted.

Rating: 4
The dill pickle is the answer. I poured about 1/8 c. of the pickle juice over the slightly warm cubed potatoes and let that soak in before I proceeded with the rest of the recipe. My family could not get enough. This is rates as one of the best potato salads I have ever had!

